Company: The Guidance Center of Westchester, Inc.
Description of incident: On February 22, 2013, the Guidance Center of Westchester discovered that a central processing unit (CPU) had been removed form a staff member's office.  The CPU was removed on February 21 and contained, names, Social Security numbers, dates of birth, dates of admittance to the Center, names of insurance carriers, home addresses, diagnoses, outpatient treatment authorization request, doctors' names, case numbers, and whether or not a patient was prescribed medication.
